webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Letter card with an age-old lens purchase view. The open surface was at the time called Sankt Larstorget. For the time elder, the Landskyrkosquare was named because of its location near the church of the parish, Sankt Larskyrkan, which glimpses into the right picture edge. Quickly opposite the church, Lköpping’s old theatre, the Assemblé and the spectacle house rises - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240129. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017433162. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
